# The modification procedure for the ''removal of baffles from stock motorcycle exhaust canisters''.  Since at least the early 1970's, both motorcycle racers and enthusiasts alike have been removing the baffles from motorcycle exhausts in search of increased exhaust flow and a change in the sound of the exhaust note.  Although improved performance is not the primary goal of this motorcycle modification procedure, peformance gains have been reported when this process is combined with fuel management system modifications and dyno tuning.


Coring the stock cannisters and removing the baffles is often used as an inexpensive alternative to purchasing costly aftermarket slipon exhaust systems. 

